Class Food

java.lang.Object
Food
public class Food
extends java.lang.Object
This class is the template for creating the Food objects in the Thanksgiving class. This class has one three-argument constructor and seven instance methods (four getter methods and three setter methods). It also contains four private instance variables.
Since:
10/24/21
Author:
Tucker Dickson

  • Field Summary

    Fields 
    Modifier and Type Field Description
    private double enjoyment
    This private double represents the enjoyment value of this food object.
    private double evRatio
    This private double represents the enjoyment-to-volume ratio of this food object, expressed as evRatio = enjoyment / volume
    private java.lang.String name
    This private String represents the name of this food object (ie: turkey).
    private double volume
    This private double represents the volume occupied by this food object.

  • Constructor Details

    • Food

      public Food​(double volume, double enjoyment, java.lang.String name)
      This is the sole constructor for the Food class. It takes in three arguments and uses them to initialize volume, enjoyment, and name, respectively. It also initializes evRatio by diving enjoyment by volume.
      Parameters:
      volume - This double is used to initialize the volume instance variable.
      enjoyment - This double is used to initialize the enjoyment instance variable.
      name - This String is used to initialize the name instance variable.

    • getEvRatio

      public double getEvRatio()

    • setVolume

      public void setVolume​(double volume)
      This method acts as the "setter" method for the volume instance variable. It takes in one double as a parameter and uses it to set volume. If the value of the parameter is less than zero, an error message is printed and volume gets initialized to one.
      Parameters:
      volume - This double is used to initialize the volume instance variable.

    • setEnjoyment

      public void setEnjoyment​(double enjoyment)
      This method acts as the "setter" method for the enjoyment instance variable. It takes in one double as a parameter and uses it to set enjoyment. If the value of the parameter is less than zero, an error message is printed and enjoyment gets initialized to one.
      Parameters:
      enjoyment - This double is used to initialize the enjoyment instance variable.

    • setEvRatio

      public void setEvRatio()
      This method acts as the "setter" method for the evRatio instance variable. Unlike most setters, this method does not take any parameters; it simply sets evRatio to the quotient of enjoyment and volume.
